OL,3,CLaos methanol poisoning families
OL,4,C'crushed' over expected charges
OL,6,FAustralia's Department of Foreign
OL,7,FAffairs and Trade (DFAT) said of its
OL,8,Fcorrespondence with the Laos
OL,9,Fgovernment: "The explanation provided
OL,10,Fsuggested the Prosecutor does not
OL,11,Fconsider they have sufficient evidence
OL,12,Fto establish the necessary legal link
OL,13,Fbetween the Tiger alcohol and the
OL,14,Fdeaths of Holly and Bianca."
OL,16,FThe two Australian women had been
OL,17,Fstaying at the Nana Backpacker Hostel,
OL,18,Fwhere they reportedly consumed "free
OL,19,Fshots" of Laotian vodka before heading
OL,20,Fout to other venues.
OL,26,@qD@MOUvD@\O]zD@`OU{D@FO]
