CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784292510
OL,3,CLaos methanol poisoning families
OL,4,C'crushed' over expected charges
OL,6,FOn Wednesday, the UK government
OL,7,Flaunched a new campaign with survivors
OL,8,Fand families linked to methanol
OL,9,Fpoisonings to try and prevent further
OL,10,Ftragedies abroad.
OL,12,FIt encourages travellers to be careful
OL,13,Fwhen drinking abroad and to
OL,14,Ffamiliarise themselves with the
OL,15,Fsymptoms of having unknowingly
OL,16,Fconsumed methanol-contaminated alcohol.
OL,18,FThere are no details yet as to how
OL,19,Fmany people are due to be charged in
OL,20,Frelation to the poisonings.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
